# Modulo billing

Escopo
- Responsavel por planos de assinatura e checkout de pagamento.
- Todo fluxo de cobranca deve passar por este modulo.

Rotas e entradas
- Stack: `src/modules/billing/presentation/stacks/billing.stack.tsx`.
- Base path: `/billing`.
- Pages:
  - `landing`: `presentation/pages/landing/landing.page`.
  - `plans`: `presentation/pages/plan-selection/plan-selection.page`.
  - `checkout`: `presentation/pages/checkout/checkout.page`.

Modelos principais (billing-api.ts)
- `BillingPlan`: id, dbId, name, description, currency, priceCents (monthly/yearly), features, recommended.
- `PaymentConfig`: gateway (mercadopago), publicKey, configured.
- `CheckoutRequest`: planId, billingCycle, payer, paymentMethod, cardToken, installments, urls, metadata, workspaceId, userUid.
- `CheckoutResponse`: status, tipo (card/preference), checkoutUrl, plan, amount, currency.

Services
- `billing.service.ts`
  - Cache com `BehaviorSubject` (`plans$`).
  - Resolve `workspaceId` via `companyService`.
  - Resolve `userUid` via `usersAuthService`.
  - Monta headers `x-workspace-id` e `x-user-uid`.
  - `fetchPlans()` busca planos e cacheia.
  - `createCheckout()` monta payload completo e chama API.
- `billing-api.ts`
  - Endpoints: `GET /billing/plans`, `POST /billing/checkout`.

Integracoes
- Depende de `companyService` (workspace).
- Depende de `usersAuthService` (sessao).
- Usa `httpClient` do `core`.

Guardrails
- Nunca chamar endpoints de billing diretamente na UI; sempre via service.
- Sempre garantir `workspaceId` e `userUid` no checkout.
- Qualquer novo metodo de pagamento deve ser padronizado aqui.
